Review: Ugh LOVE! Feels like a plot we all know, but it’s so beautifully stylized that it feels fresh. The gags are fantastic, and had me chuckling all throughout. And the chemistry the entire cast had was addictive. Can’t believe I missed this one!
Cute! Fell off at the end, wanted more Anna Kendrick, but most of the jokes landed and I loved the soundtrack
Had me sobbin like a lil baby
Jeez, can’t believe it took me this long to watch. Fantastic on all fronts. And boy do I love a fish eye lens.
Tbh I only saw the second half, but it was a great second half! Simon Pegg was my most watched actor of 2023 so slay
So much fun! Perfect day off movie. And I love my girl Ritu Arya, one of the funniest physical comedy actors working rn, please go watch the Umbrella Academy
Sobbed like a baby. Why did no one warn me that this was literally the saddest movie in the world. Happy fucking new year jeez
Biggest pet peeve is when you’re shooting a movie and you score the absolute perfect location and you only use that to your advantage for a fraction of the film. Booo
